com.satori.rtm

Interface SubscriptionListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SubscriptionAdapter

    public interface SubscriptionListener
    Defines callback methods for events in the subscription lifecycle.

    To set this for a subscription, call RtmClient.createSubscription() or instantiate a SubscriptionConfig with a SubscriptionListener (SubscriptionConfig.SubscriptionConfig(EnumSet, SubscriptionListener))

    SubscriptionAdapter is an empty implementation of this interface.

    • Method Detail

      • onCreated

        void onCreated()
        Called when a subscription is created.

        You can create a subscription even if your the client isn't connected to RTM. The RTM SDK manages the subscription workflow and sends the actual request when the client connects to RTM.

      • onDeleted

        void onDeleted()
        Called when a subscription is deleted.

      • onEnterUnsubscribed

        void onEnterUnsubscribed(UnsubscribeRequest request,
                         UnsubscribeReply reply)
        Called when a subscription enters the unsubscribed state. This is the initial state for the subscription lifecycle.

        A subscription enters this state in the following situations:

        • The subscription was created and initialized with the unsubscribed state
        • The connection is dropped
        • RtmClient.removeSubscription() method is called
        Parameters:
        request - unsubscribe request PDU
        reply - unsubscribe response PDU

      • onLeaveUnsubscribed

        void onLeaveUnsubscribed(UnsubscribeRequest request,
                         UnsubscribeReply reply)
        Called when a subscription leaves the unsubscribed state. unsubscribed is the initial state for the subscription lifecycle.

        A subscription leaves this state when connection is established

        Parameters:
        request - unsubscribe request PDU
        reply - unsubscribe response PDU

      • onEnterSubscribing

        void onEnterSubscribing(SubscribeRequest request)
        Called when a subscription enters the subscribing state.

        A subscription enters this state when the client is attempting to subscribe to a channel.

        Parameters:
        request - subscribe request PDU

      • onLeaveSubscribing

        void onLeaveSubscribing(SubscribeRequest request)
        Called when a subscription leaves the subscribing state.

        A subscription leaves this state when the subscribe request completes successfully or fails.

        Parameters:
        request - subscribe request PDU.

      • onEnterSubscribed

        void onEnterSubscribed(SubscribeRequest request,
                       SubscribeReply reply)
        Called when a subscription enters the subscribed state.

        A subscription enters this state when the subscribe request completes successfully and an acknowledgement from RTM is received.

        Parameters:
        request - subscribe request PDU
        reply - subscribe reply PDU

      • onLeaveSubscribed

        void onLeaveSubscribed(SubscribeRequest request,
                       SubscribeReply reply)
        Called when a subscription leaves the subscribed state.

        A subscription leaves the state when you're no longer subscribed to the channel. For example, the subscription leaves this state when you explicitly remove the subscription from the channel or the connection drops.

        Parameters:
        request - subscribe request PDU
        reply - subscribe reply PDU

      • onEnterUnsubscribing

        void onEnterUnsubscribing(UnsubscribeRequest request)
        Called when a subscription enters unsubscribing state.

        A subscription enters this state when the client attempts to unsubscribe by calling RtmClient.removeSubscription().

        Parameters:
        request - unsubscribe request PDU

      • onLeaveUnsubscribing

        void onLeaveUnsubscribing(UnsubscribeRequest request)
        Called when a subscription leaves the unsubscribing state.

        A subscription leaves this state when the unsubscribe request completes successfully or fails.

        Parameters:
        request - unsubscribe request PDU.

      • onEnterFailed

        void onEnterFailed()
        Called when a subscription enters the failed state.

        A subscription enters this state when a channel error is sent from RTM.

      • onLeaveFailed

        void onLeaveFailed()
        Called when a subscription leaves the failed state.

        A subscription leaves this state when the client disconnects or user removes subscription explicitly.

      • onSubscriptionData

        void onSubscriptionData(SubscriptionData data)
        Called when the client receives a message from RTM that was published to the subscription.
        Parameters:
        data - Subscription data PDU.

      • onSubscriptionError

        void onSubscriptionError(SubscriptionError error)
        Called when the client receives a subscription error from RTM.
        Parameters:
        error - Subscription error.

      • onSubscriptionInfo

        void onSubscriptionInfo(SubscriptionInfo info)
        Called when the client receives a subscription info from RTM.
        Parameters:
        info - Subscription info body.
